### Example 10: Visualizing Riemann bars—f(x)=x², [0,2], n=8

```scheme
(define (f x) (* x x))

(define bars
  (let* ((a 0)
         (b 2)
         (n 8)
         (dx (/ (- b a) n)))
    (map (lambda (i)
           (let* ((xi (+ a (* (+ i 0.5) dx)))
                  (height (f xi)))
             (list xi height dx)))
         (iota n))))

(define pts
  (apply append
         (map (lambda (bar)
                (let ((x (car bar))
                      (h (cadr bar))
                      (w (caddr bar)))
                  (let ((x0 (- x (/ w 2)))
                        (x1 (+ x (/ w 2))))
                    (list (list x0 0)
                          (list x0 h)
                          (list x1 h)
                          (list x1 0)))))
              bars)))

(define p (plot/scatter pts))

(plot/render-svg p)
```

<!-- BUILD: run through interpreter, render SVG on Cartesian grid, x∈[0,2], y∈[0,4], bars drawn as scatter-connected polylines. -->

[VISUAL: Cartesian grid, x-axis 0 to 2, y-axis 0 to 4. Eight rectangular bars under the parabola f(x)=x², each bar centered at a midpoint sample, filling the region under the curve with visible gaps at the top where the rectangles don't quite match the parabola.]

