### Example 18: FTC Part 2—derivative of an integral

```scheme
(define (f t) (* t t))

(define (A x)
  (calc/integral f 0 x))

(define x0 2)

(define derivative-of-A (calc/derivative A x0))

(define f-at-x0 (f x0))

(display \"d/dx ∫₀ˣ t² dt at x=2: \")
(display derivative-of-A)
(newline)

(display \"f(2) = 2² = \")
(display f-at-x0)
(newline)
```

<!-- BUILD: run, print both. -->

[VISUAL: Console output shows both ≈ 4.0, confirming FTC Part 2.]

