### Example 25: Substitution inside `calc/integral`—it handles it numerically

```scheme
(define (f x)
  (* (calc/sin x) (calc/cos x)))

(define integral (calc/integral f 0 1.5708))

(display \"Integral of sin(x)cos(x) from 0 to π/2: \")
(display integral)
(newline)
```

<!-- BUILD: run, print. -->

[VISUAL: Console output: `0.5`]

u = sin(x), du = cos(x)dx, ∫ u du = u²/2 = sin²(x)/2. Eval [0,π/2]: (1 - 0)/2 = 0.5.

