### Example 33: Area between y=4-x² and y=x²+2

```scheme
(define (f x) (- 4 (* x x)))
(define (g x) (+ (* x x) 2))

(define area (calc/integral (lambda (x) (- (f x) (g x))) -1 1))

(display \"Area between 4-x² and x²+2 on [-1,1]: \")
(display area)
(newline)
```

<!-- BUILD: run, print. -->

[VISUAL: Console output: `2.666…`]

4-x² - (x²+2) = 2 - 2x². ∫[-1,1] (2-2x²) = 2x - (2/3)x³ → 4 - 4/3 = 8/3.

