## Topic 10: Infinite Series and Convergence

### History

A *series* is the sum Σ aₙ. Does the infinite sum converge? The geometric series 1 + r + r² + … = 1/(1-r) if |r|<1—known to the Greeks. The harmonic series Σ 1/n diverges—proved by Oresme in the 1300s. Convergence tests (ratio, integral, comparison) formalized by Cauchy and d'Alembert.

### Uses

Power series represent functions. Probability: normalizing constants. Signal processing: Fourier series.

---

### Example 51: Geometric series, r=1/2

```scheme
(define (partial-sum n)
  (fold + 0 (map (lambda (k) (expt 0.5 k)) (iota n 1))))

(display \"S₅ = \") (display (partial-sum 5)) (newline)
(display \"S₁₀ = \") (display (partial-sum 10)) (newline)
(display \"S₂₀ = \") (display (partial-sum 20)) (newline)
```

<!-- BUILD: run, print. -->

[VISUAL: Console output: 0.96875, 0.9990…, 0.99999…—converging to 1.]

Exact: 1/(1-0.5) - 1 = 1.

---

### Example 52: Harmonic series diverges

```scheme
(define (partial-sum n)
  (fold + 0 (map (lambda (k) (/ 1.0 k)) (iota n 1))))

(display \"S₁₀ = \") (display (partial-sum 10)) (newline)
(display \"S₁₀₀ = \") (display (partial-sum 100)) (newline)
(display \"S₁₀₀₀ = \") (display (partial-sum 1000)) (newline)
```

<!-- BUILD: run, print. -->

[VISUAL: Console output: 2.928…, 5.187…, 7.485…—growing without bound.]

---

### Example 53: Alternating harmonic series converges

```scheme
(define (partial-sum n)
  (fold + 0 (map (lambda (k) (/ (expt -1 (+ k 1)) k)) (iota n 1))))

(display \"S₁₀ = \") (display (partial-sum 10)) (newline)
(display \"S₁₀₀ = \") (display (partial-sum 100)) (newline)
(display \"S₁₀₀₀ = \") (display (partial-sum 1000)) (newline)
```

<!-- BUILD: run, print. -->

[VISUAL: Console output: 0.645…, 0.688…, 0.6926…—converging to ln 2 ≈ 0.693.]

---

### Example 54: p-series Σ 1/n²

```scheme
(define (partial-sum n)
  (fold + 0 (map (lambda (k) (/ 1.0 (* k k))) (iota n 1))))

(display \"S₁₀ = \") (display (partial-sum 10)) (newline)
(display \"S₁₀₀ = \") (display (partial-sum 100)) (newline)
(display \"S₁₀₀₀ = \") (display (partial-sum 1000)) (newline)
```

<!-- BUILD: run, print. -->

[VISUAL: Console output: 1.549…, 1.634…, 1.643…—converging to π²/6 ≈ 1.6449.]

---

### Example 55: Ratio test—does Σ n!/nⁿ converge?

```scheme
(define (term n)
  (/ (fold * 1 (iota n 1)) (expt n n)))

(display \"a₁ = \") (display (term 1)) (newline)
(display \"a₅ = \") (display (term 5)) (newline)
(display \"a₁₀ = \") (display (term 10)) (newline)
```

<!-- BUILD: run, print. -->

[VISUAL: Console output: 1.0, 0.0384, 0.000036…—terms shrink fast, series converges.]

---

