### Example 62: Radius of convergence—ln(1+x) only converges for |x|<1

```scheme
(define (taylor-ln x n)
  (fold + 0
        (map (lambda (k)
               (let ((sign (expt -1 (+ k 1)))
                     (pow (expt x k)))
                 (/ (* sign pow) k)))
             (iota n 1))))

(define x 1.5)

(display \"ln(2.5), 10 terms: \") (display (taylor-ln x 10)) (newline)
(display \"ln(2.5), 20 terms: \") (display (taylor-ln x 20)) (newline)
```

<!-- BUILD: run, print. -->

[VISUAL: Console output: terms blow up—series diverges outside radius of convergence.]

